import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'])
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the correlation between 'u' and 'v'?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist2d(data['u'], data['v'], bins=30, cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    plt.colorbar(label='Frequency')
    plt.title("What is the joint distribution of 'u' and 'v'?")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    mean_u = data['u'].mean()
    std_u = data['u'].std()
    mean_v = data['v'].mean()
    std_v = data['v'].std()
    
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'], label="Data points")
    plt.axvline(mean_u, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean u: {mean_u:.2f}")
    plt.axhline(mean_v, color='g', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean v: {mean_v:.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    
    plt.title("What is the mean and standard deviation of 'u' and 'v'?")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
